  "response": "Cannibals are individuals or members of a species that consume the flesh or internal organs of members of their own species. When referring specifically to humans, **human cannibalism** involves one person eating another person. This practice has occurred in various cultures and contexts throughout history for several reasons:\n\n1. **Survival Situations**: In extreme conditions, such as famines or shipwrecks, individuals have resorted to cannibalism to survive. A well-known example is the Donner Party, a group of American pioneers who became stranded in the Sierra Nevada during the winter of 1846-1847 and resorted to cannibalism.\n\n2. **Ritualistic or Religious Practices**: Some cultures have engaged in ritualistic cannibalism as part of religious ceremonies or spiritual beliefs. For instance, certain indigenous tribes in the Amazon and Papua New Guinea have practiced endocannibalism (consuming members of one's own community) as a form of honoring the dead.\n\n3. **Warfare and Domin",
